Show navigation Hide navigation Home About Location Inaugural Season 2016-17 Hornets Sports & Entertainment is proud to announce that the city of Greensboro and the Greensboro Coliseum Complex have been selected as the home of our new NBA Development League team. Join the Swarm for their inaugural season! A brand new team of talented basketball players will showcase their heart and skills during 24 home games right here in Greensboro. A Swarm Season Membership offers big savings as compared to single game ticket prices and great benefits! Season Membership pricing has been released and you can place a $25 deposit now to secure your seats. Once a deposit is made, a Swarm representative will contact you regarding seat selection. Swarm Season Ticket Member Benefits Seating Chart / Pricing To enlarge, please click on the seating chart below Press Releases D-League Team Announcement Logo for D-League Team Revealed Season Ticket Info Available About Us. The new NBA D-League team’s offices will also be located in the Greensboro Coliseum Complex, on the second floor of the Greensboro Area Convention and Visitors Bureau building. The business operations will be led by Steve Swetoha, who has been named by Hornets Sports & Entertainment as President of the team. Swetoha, who brings over 20 years of experience in the sports industry, spent the last six years as President and Chief Revenue Officer of the WNBA’s Tulsa Shock. In Tulsa, he was responsible for all aspects of the organization and secured one of the league’s largest jersey marquee deals. Swetoha is no stranger to the Hornets or the state of North Carolina, having previously served as Senior Vice President of Ticket Sales & Services for the then-Charlotte Bobcats and Vice President of Business Operations for the WNBA’s Charlotte Sting. He was also Executive Director of the ACC Football Championship game held in Charlotte in December 2010. How many teams are in the NBA Development League? There are an all-time high 19 NBA D-League teams heading into the 2015-16 season, each of which is singly affiliated with one NBA team: Austin Spurs (San Antonio Spurs), Bakersfield Jam (Phoenix Suns), Canton Charge (Cleveland Cavaliers), Delaware 87ers (Philadelphia 76ers), Erie BayHawks (Orlando Magic), Fort Wayne Mad Ants (Indiana Pacers), Grand Rapids Drive (Detroit Pistons), Idaho Stampede (Utah Jazz), Iowa Energy (Memphis Grizzlies), Los Angeles D-Fenders (Los Angeles Lakers), Maine Red Claws (Boston Celtics), Oklahoma City Blue (Oklahoma City Thunder), Raptors 905 (Toronto Raptors), Reno Bighorns (Sacramento Kings), Rio Grande Valley Vipers (Houston Rockets), Santa Cruz Warriors (Golden State Warriors), Sioux Falls Skyforce (Miami Heat), Texas Legends (Dallas Mavericks), Westchester Knicks (New York Knicks). What is the NBA Development League? The NBA Development League, or NBA D-League, is the NBA’s official minor league, preparing players, coaches, officials, trainers and front office staff for the NBA while acting as the league’s research and development laboratory. How many games are in an NBA Development League season? Each NBA D-League teams plays a 50-game regular season schedule, which begins in November and runs into April. The Swarm will play 24 home games in Greensboro. In April, the playoffs consist of three rounds, all of which follow a best-of-three series format. How many NBA Development League players have made it to the NBA? A record 170 players with NBA D-League experience were on NBA rosters at the end of the 2014-15 regular season, representing an all-time high 38 percent of the league. Notable D-League Players. Greensboro D-League Message. Thank you for your interest in our Greensboro D-League team! We are looking for great talent to be part of this new team. All of our currently open roles – for both Greensboro and Charlotte – are posted at TeamWork Online. If you have interest in a particular role, we encourage you to apply for consideration. We will staff a variety of positons over the next year as we lead up to our inaugural season (Fall 2016). To stay-up-to-date on available positions, you may want to apply for Notification of Jobs in the Future found on our TeamWork Online page, this way you will be one of the first to know when we’ve posted new positions. Also, you can join us on LinkedIn where we share information about a variety of positions and hiring events. We appreciate your interest and hope to see you as part of our process! More Questions? Looking for more information on our team? Try our FAQ section. Download the FAQ Address. 1921 W Gate City Blvd Greensboro, NC 27403 Phone Numbers. Phone: (336) 907-3600 Emails. dleague@hornets.com Something went wrong... Unable to load map... Please try to enable javascript This refundable deposit in the amount of $25 per seat shall secure your option to purchase season ticket seating for the D-League team affiliate of the Charlotte Hornets playing games during the 2016-2017 D-League season in Greensboro, North Carolina. In the event you elect to purchase season tickets for the 2016-2017 D-League season, your deposit shall be applied to the amount of the season ticket. In the event you do not elect to purchase season tickets for the 2016-2017 D-League season, you must request a refund, in writing to Hornets Sports & Entertainment, 333 East Trade Street, Charlotte, NC 28202, said request to be made within forty-five (45) days of the date season tickets first go on sale. In the event that you do not request a refund within those forty-five (45) days, the deposit shall stay on your account for one (1) year and may be applied to partial ticket plans or group tickets. © Copyright 2015 Hornets Sports & Entertainment Maintained by Hornets.com
